ast majority of Christian Right leaders encourage their followers to embrace deliberative norms in the public square, including civility and secular reasoning. At the same time, Shields highlights a tension between participatory and deliberative ideals since Christian Right leaders also nurture moral passions, prejudices, and dogmas to propel their movement. Nonetheless, the Christian Right's other democratic virtues help contain civic extremism, sharpen the thinking of activists, and raise the level and tenor of political debate for all Americans.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 08. Jul 2019) 0aChristian conservatismzUnited States. 0aChristianity and politicszUnited States. 0aReligious rightzUnited States. 7aRELIGION / Religion, Politics & State.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertPUP eBook-Package 2000-2015z978311066258008iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertPrinceton eBook Package Backlist 2000-2013z978311044250208iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertPrinceton eBook Package Backlist 2000-2014z978311045953140uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9781400830107423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9781400830107.jpg  a978-3-11-044250-2  Princeton eBook Package Backlist 2000-2013c2000d2013  a978-3-11-045953-1  Princeton eBook Package Backlist 2000-2014c2000d2014  a978-3-11-066258-0  PUP eBook-Package 2000-2015  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_PLTLJSIS  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_PLTLJSIS  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA14ALL  aPDA16SSH  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA1ALL  aPDA2  aPDA2HUM  aPDA5EBK  aPDA7ENG  aPDA9PRIN